Usage: nag <command>

where <command> is one of:
    config, edit, help, quiz

nag <cmd> -h     quick help on <cmd>
nag -l           display full usage info
nag faq          commonly asked questions
nag help <term>  search for help on <term>
nag help nag     involved overview

Specify configs in the ini-formatted file:
    /Users/rich/.npmrc
or on the command line via: npm <command> --key value
Config info can be viewed via: npm help config

npm@2.1.18 /usr/local/lib/node_modules/npm
